{
  "texts": [
    "The tubes were then centrifuged for 5 min at 5,200g at room temperature to isolate the plasma supernatant.",
    "Test compounds were received as powder and solubilized at various concentrations in 0.9% aqueous sodium chloride solution and adjusted for pH with phosphate-buffered saline (PBS).",
    "The assay was conducted in 384-well plates.",
    "Rat plasma (10 μl) was added to 10 μl of the various compound solutions.",
    "A total of 10 μl of vehicle (0.9% aqueous sodium chloride solution, PBS) added to the plasma was used as a negative control."
  ]
}